Peel and grate the @garlic clove{2}(peeled and grated) (or use a #garlic press{}).

Trim the @pak choi{1}(trimmed), then thinly slice widthways. Trim and halve the @green beans{80%grams}(trimmed and halved).

Zest and halve the @lime{1}(zested and halved).

Heat a drizzle of @oil{} in a large #saucepan{} on high heat.

Once hot, add the @sliced mushrooms{120%grams} to the pan and fry, stirring occasionally, until browned, ~{5-6%minutes}.

Stir the @red Thai style paste{75%grams}, @Thai style spice mix{1%sachet} (add less if you'd prefer things milder) and garlic into the mushrooms.

Stir fry for ~{1%minute}.

Pour the @coconut milk{200%milliliter}, @soy sauce{25%milliliter}, @sugar{1%tsp} and @water for the soup{200%milliliter} into the pan.

Bring to the boil, then add the green beans and the pak choi. Simmer until just tender, ~{4-6%minutes}.

Add the @udon noodles{220%grams} to the soup and cook until warmed through, ~{1-2%minutes}.

Remove the saucepan from the heat. Stir in the lime zest and half of the lime juice.

Taste the soup and add more @?salt{}, @?black pepper{}, lime juice or sugar if needed.

Share the udon noodle soup between your #bowls{}.

Cut any remaining lime into wedges for squeezing over.

> This delicious Red Thai Style Udon Noodle Soup has been expertly designed by our chefs as a lighter option to help with a balanced lifestyle.